public class Jeo
extends ScriptHelper

Java Entity Object (JEO), pronounced Jay-Oh, is a data wrapper and collection object which can be extended to provide application-specific data services.

           Script aScript)
Construct an instance by name and pass a constructed Script.

Parameters:
aInstanceName - The logical name given to this instance.
aScript - To be used by sub-classed instances. The Jeo superclass has no dependency on nor does it use a Script object. This is provided for subclasses that may need to perform Script related functions.

Parameters:
